Package gw.cc.financials.check.entity

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Check
    Check Groups one or more payments together for payment by a single check.
    CheckGroup
    CheckGroup Groups the checks that share a set of payments.
    CheckPayee
    CheckPayee Links a check to its payees.
    CheckPortion
    CheckPortion Indicates the amount that applies to a check.
    CheckRecurrence
    CheckRecurrence Describes the recurrence schedule for a check.
    CheckRpt
    CheckRpt Calculated amounts for checks.
    CheckSearchView
    CheckSearchView View entity for efficiently displaying Checks on the Payment/Check search page.
    CheckSet
    CheckSet A check submitted for approval.
    CheckSetReserve
    CheckSetReserve Links a check set with any reserves that were automatically created as part of processing the payment.
    CheckView
    CheckView View entity for efficiently displaying Checks in list views.
    Deduction
    Deduction A deduction from a Check.
    MonthlyCheckRecurrence
    MonthlyCheckRecurrence A monthly recurrence schedule.
    RecurringCheck
    RecurringCheck Groups the occurrences of a check across a recurrence
    TmpCheckRpt
    TmpCheckRpt temp table used for recalculating CheckRpt.GrossAmount values
    TmpCheckRptCheckGroup
    TmpCheckRptCheckGroup Temp table used for recalculating CheckRpt.GrossAmount values for checks that are part of a group (i.e., primary and secondary payee checks)
    TmpCheckRptIgnorePmts
    TmpCheckRptIgnorePmts Temp table used to store IDs of offsetting payments for voided/stopped checks, which should not be included in checkrpt grossamount values
    TmpCheckSet
    TmpCheckSet Temp table for upgrade to argo checksets.
    TmpMixedCheckGroups
    TmpMixedCheckGroups Temp table used to store IDs of CheckGroups that have a mixture of canceled (i.e., voided/stopped) and non-canceled checks.
    WeeklyCheckRecurrence
    WeeklyCheckRecurrence A weekly recurrence schedule.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Check.CheckConstants
